08/04/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The government decided on Thursday (7 April) to hold local elections on 15 May. 
Voters will elect 426 municipal and 123 town councils, 20 county assemblies and a new Zagreb city assembly. 
The elections will be organised by county and municipal election commissions, whose work will be supervised by the State Election Commission. 
Campaigning officially begins on 24 April. 
The last local elections were held in May 2001. 
(Vecernji List - 08/04/05; HINA - 07/04/05)
